1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,211
<i>We can pay you! Please let me go already.</i>

2
00:00:03,294 --> 00:00:04,671
- [DADO] <i>Shut up. Shut up!</i>
- [MUFFLED GRUNT]

3
00:00:04,754 --> 00:00:08,341
[EMIL] <i>We need backup here.</i>
<i>We're outnumbered.</i>

4
00:00:09,968 --> 00:00:11,553
[BEN] <i>Ma'am, I'm sorry,</i>

5
00:00:11,636 --> 00:00:15,181
<i>but I'll only speak up once about</i>
<i>what you did to my daughter.</i>

6
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:16,266
<i>What I did?</i>

7
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:19,102
<i>And what about what you did</i>
<i>back then, Wendy?</i>

8
00:00:21,604 --> 00:00:23,690
- [JOY] <i>There's the speedboat!</i>
- [LIAM]<i> Come on!</i>

9
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:25,024
[GUNSHOTS]

10
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:26,401
[EMIL] <i>You're not going anywhere!</i>

11
00:00:26,484 --> 00:00:28,945
- [LIAM] <i>Let him go!</i>
<i>- Why should I follow your orders?</i>

12
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:31,698
[LIAM] <i>Because if you don't</i>
<i>do as I say, I'm going to kill Leni!</i>

13
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,199
- [GUNSHOT]
- [SCREAMING]

14
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:34,492
<i>Leni!</i>

15
00:00:34,576 --> 00:00:36,202
<i>Liam might be there. Let's hurry!</i>

16
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:37,620
[GUNSHOTS]

17
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:39,372
<i>- Liam!</i>
<i>- Sir Liam!</i>

18
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:45,211
[GUNSHOTS]

19
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:47,130
- [MUFFLED SCREAMS]
<i>- Hey!</i>

20
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:50,300
<i>Run!</i>

21
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:51,259
<i>Move!</i>

22
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:53,720
<i>- You're strong, Liam! Come on!</i>
- [LUNA GRUNTS]

23
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:57,140
[EXPLOSIONS]

24
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:02,103
[EMIL] Just a bit more, dear.

25
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:04,314
We're close.

26
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:06,691
We'll compress and treat your wound.

27
00:01:06,775 --> 00:01:08,401
Open the door!

28
00:01:09,986 --> 00:01:11,196
[GRUNTS]

29
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:15,241
[EMIL] Bring her to the couch.
[GRUNTS]

30
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:17,077
Bring me the alcohol! Hurry!

31
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:22,082
Bring towels too!
Hurry, get me the towels!

32
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:23,958
Hang in there, okay? Give it to me!

33
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:25,502
[LENI CRIES SOFTLY]

34
00:01:25,585 --> 00:01:28,505
Keep the pressure on it
to lessen the bleeding.

35
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,965
- It hurts, Pa!
- It's okay.

36
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:32,550
Endure it for a bit.

37
00:01:32,634 --> 00:01:33,843
[GRUNTS]

38
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:36,137
It's okay. Keep the pressure on it.

39
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:38,765
- [LENI COUGHS]
- [EMIL GRUNTS]

40
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:40,600
Give me the alcohol.

41
00:01:40,683 --> 00:01:42,060
Here.

42
00:01:42,143 --> 00:01:43,436
- [SCREAMS] Pa!
- Endure it.

43
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:44,604
- [GROANING, SCREAMING]
- Breathe!

44
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:47,774
Hang in there! Endure it!
You can do it!

45
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:49,442
Hand me the scissors!

46
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:53,279
Hang in there, dear.

47
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:55,406
Keep the pressure on the wound.

48
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:57,200
[COUGHS]

49
00:01:58,076 --> 00:01:59,869
- [GOON] Sir…
- [EMIL] You're okay.

50
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:01,830
[GRUNTING]

51
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:03,623
Give me the towel!

52
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:06,292
Alcohol!

53
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:08,169
- It hurts, Pa.
- Deep breaths.

54
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:09,420
Deep breaths!

55
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:10,630
You can do it.

56
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:11,714
[LENI AND EMIL GROAN]

57
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:13,007
- Pa, it hurts!
- Breathe.

58
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,676
Give me that. One more.

59
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:15,802
One more.

60
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,345
Bite this. Come on.

61
00:02:17,428 --> 00:02:19,430
Come on, dear. It's okay.

62
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:21,182
[EMIL BREATHES HEAVILY]

63
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:35,822
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

64
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:11,232
[MACKY PANTING]

65
00:03:15,069 --> 00:03:16,821
[GRUNTS, PANTS]

66
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:23,369
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:26,456
[DADO] Mm.

68
00:03:26,539 --> 00:03:27,665
Where are you going?

69
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:41,137
[NEWS ANCHOR]
<i>A hostage situation is currently unfolding</i>

70
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,890
<i>at the popular and exclusive</i>
<i>island destination,</i>

71
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:45,975
<i>La Playa Roja.</i>

72
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:52,857
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:59,989
<i>It is still uncertain as to what</i>
<i>the hostage takers want,</i>

74
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:02,367
<i>and who exactly are still in the resort.</i>

75
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:06,955
<i>But we are receiving various reports</i>
<i>that several high-profile guests</i>

76
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:09,540
<i>are among those</i>
<i>who are trapped on the island.</i>

77
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:20,760
[REPORTER] <i>On that side,</i>

78
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:24,847
<i>you'll only need a 30-minute boat ride</i>
<i>to reach La Playa Roja.</i>

79
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:28,268
<i>Who would've thought that</i>
<i>something terrifying</i>

80
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:31,604
<i>was happening on that island resort</i>
<i>that's a few kilometers away</i>

81
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:34,899
<i>from this quiet and peaceful dock?</i>

82
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:45,326
Dr. Morillo, Mrs. Morillo,

83
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:50,123
Major Domingo sends his thanks
for all your help in our investigation.

84
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:54,669
Sir, how can you ensure the safety of
my parents once we leave this place?

85
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:56,838
[KIANNA] He's right.

86
00:04:56,921 --> 00:04:58,798
And we just heard the news.

87
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:01,676
Two of the escaped hostages are now dead.

88
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:02,927
W-Who?

89
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,472
A Jules Santos and a Mama Ona Chan.

90
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:08,516
But… she was just here.

91
00:05:08,599 --> 00:05:10,226
You know, Jules.

92
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,603
We're still investigating if
what happened to them

93
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:16,232
had something to do with what's
happening at La Playa Roja.

94
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:18,276
[SCOFFS] Sir.

95
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:20,028
Of course they're connected!

96
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,281
[MARCO] Sir, what makes you so sure

97
00:05:23,364 --> 00:05:25,575
that what happened to them
won't happen to my parents?

98
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:28,286
Don't worry. We'll bring them
to a safe house.

99
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:29,871
There will be security 24/7,

100
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:32,832
and only immediate family
will be able to visit them.

101
00:05:32,915 --> 00:05:35,251
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

102
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,336
Mom, Dad,

103
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,715
you don't have to do this.

104
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:43,843
Kianna's right, Ma, Pa.

105
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:47,180
[MARCO] Why don't we just leave
as a whole family?

106
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:50,016
Your visas are okay.
I can book us a flight to the US.

107
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:52,685
From the hospital,
let's go straight to the airport.

108
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:58,566
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:06:06,824 --> 00:06:09,619
Sir, what's the status of the
hostage-taking incident at La Playa Roja?

110
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:12,080
[OFFICER 1] We'll call
a press briefing at the station

111
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:14,082
once we have all the information.

112
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:16,501
What about the other hostages?

113
00:06:16,584 --> 00:06:18,878
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]
- Oh.

114
00:06:18,961 --> 00:06:21,881
- [REPORTER 1] Sir! Will you file a case?
- [OFFICER 2] Make way!

115
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:23,716
- Can I ask a question?
- Wait. Excuse me.

116
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,093
Can we do an interview, sir?

117
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:27,428
- How are you doing?
- Get in the car. Come on.

118
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:28,888
Get in. Hurry.

119
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:30,932
- Ma'am, get in.
- [REPORTER 2] How do you feel?

120
00:06:31,015 --> 00:06:33,142
- [REPORTER 3] Sir!
- Son, take care, okay?

121
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:34,727
Dad, you're not coming?

122
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:40,191
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

123
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:46,739
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:48,741
- [REPORTER 3] How are you--
- [REPORTER 4] Sir!

125
00:06:55,873 --> 00:06:58,501
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

126
00:06:58,584 --> 00:07:01,629
[PHONE RINGING]

127
00:07:02,421 --> 00:07:03,881
Yes, baby?

128
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:08,761
[KIANNA] Yes, they're with us now.

129
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:10,596
You want to talk to them?

130
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:13,349
Okay. Wait.

131
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,184
Mom.

132
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:16,644
Okay.

133
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:19,272
Hi, dear.

134
00:07:19,355 --> 00:07:21,941
Hello, Grandma. Hello, Grandpa.

135
00:07:22,024 --> 00:07:23,901
We miss you.

136
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,069
Hi, dear.

137
00:07:25,903 --> 00:07:27,280
We miss you so much.

138
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:31,701
<i>I miss you too. How was your vacation?</i>

139
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:33,244
Oh…

140
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:35,455
We had fun. Yes, we had fun.

141
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:37,582
<i>That's great.</i>

142
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:39,500
<i>Are you coming home now?</i>

143
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:43,212
[CONNEY] Yes. W-We're on our way home.

144
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:46,549
<i>Okay. Don't forget my gift.</i>

145
00:07:46,632 --> 00:07:49,010
Of course, we bought you a gift.

146
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:50,887
[CONNEY] Okay?

147
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:54,515
I love you, Grandma. I love you, Grandpa.

148
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:55,975
Mwah!

149
00:07:56,058 --> 00:07:57,768
Okay, here's your mom.

150
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,438
Thanks, Mom.

151
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:26,964
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:08:29,884 --> 00:08:31,552
Be strong.

153
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:34,388
Olsen is with the police

154
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:35,640
and Magnus.

155
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:38,935
That doesn't make it better, Pa.

156
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:44,941
I shouldn't have allowed Olsen to leave,
no matter who he was with.

157
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,195
Who can stop your son?

158
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:51,239
He takes after you.

159
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:53,324
Stubborn.

160
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:59,830
What did Ma'am Greta mean earlier?

161
00:08:59,914 --> 00:09:01,415
Why does it seem

162
00:09:02,124 --> 00:09:04,961
like she's implying you did
something to her before?

163
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:13,553
Pa…

164
00:09:14,845 --> 00:09:17,223
I've known Greta for a long time.

165
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:19,183
She likes bringing up the past.

166
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:23,437
When she does something wrong,
she blames it on someone else.

167
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,231
She thinks she's always right.

168
00:09:25,314 --> 00:09:27,900
She thinks she's better
than everyone else.

169
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,945
So you two are like your sons?

170
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:33,614
You're on bad terms now?

171
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:36,117
Pa, she's crossing the line.

172
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:40,871
[MAN] Help!

173
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:47,753
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

174
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:50,256
- [WENDY] Olsen, what happened to Liam?
- He got shot.

175
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:51,924
- [GRETA] Liam!
- [OLSEN] Bring him inside.

176
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:53,384
[GRETA] Liam, son! Liam!

177
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:54,719
- [BEN] Ma'am.
- [GRETA] Liam!

178
00:09:54,802 --> 00:10:01,726
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

179
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:03,644
[GRETA SOBS]

180
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,941
[GRETA CRIES]

181
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:18,492
[GRETA WHIMPERING]

182
00:10:21,203 --> 00:10:25,207
[BOAT ENGINE REVVING]

183
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:29,462
[JOY] Manager Happy, we're finally safe.

184
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:31,213
[JOY SOBS]

185
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:33,549
[SOBS]

186
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,134
Thank you so much.

187
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,721
Be careful. Let's go.

188
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:42,892
[GRUNTS]

189
00:10:46,395 --> 00:10:47,480
[JOY GRUNTS]

190
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:50,816
[JOY EXHALES SHARPLY]

191
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,360
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

192
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:54,403
[REPORTER 1] How did you escape?

193
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:56,864
- [OFFICERS] Please step back.
- How did you escape?

194
00:10:56,947 --> 00:10:58,741
- That's enough.
- Please stop.

195
00:10:58,824 --> 00:11:01,077
They need to be treated.

196
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,495
- Ma'am!
- Ma'am, just a minute!

197
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:04,163
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

198
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:06,040
[OFFICER 1] Ma'am, that's enough.

199
00:11:06,123 --> 00:11:08,709
- Let them pass through.
- Enough.

200
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:11,712
[REPORTERS KEEP CLAMORING]

201
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:13,672
- Stop.
- Please step back.

202
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,800
Please leave them alone.

203
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:18,761
[REPORTER 2] Just a bit.
Just one question.

204
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:21,722
Please step back. Sir, please move.

205
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:23,182
[OFFICER 2] Sir, please move.

206
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:25,226
They need to get medical treatment, sir.

207
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:27,186
[OFFICER 3] They need to get treated.

208
00:11:27,269 --> 00:11:28,270
[OFFICER 4] That's enough.

209
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:32,400
[REPORTER 3] Do you think the people
left at La Playa Roja are still alive?

210
00:11:32,483 --> 00:11:36,028
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING,
SLOWLY SUBSIDING]

211
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:38,739
- Olsen.
- Ma.

212
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:44,412
Have some of this. It's from the police.

213
00:11:47,957 --> 00:11:49,750
- How about you?
- I've already eaten.

214
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:51,919
Go on, eat it.

215
00:11:57,967 --> 00:11:59,969
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]
- You don't want to eat?

216
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:02,638
I'll eat it when I get hungry later.

217
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,057
You can have that.

218
00:12:06,016 --> 00:12:12,356
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

219
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:18,487
What are you doing, Ma?

220
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:21,407
I'm just checking.

221
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:26,078
You might have wounds
and just not be telling me.

222
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:29,457
I promise, it's not like that. Hey.

223
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:31,208
Hey. Hey.

224
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:34,211
- I'm just worried.
- Don't be.

225
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:36,714
I'm not hurt, okay?

226
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:39,341
Okay?

227
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,886
- I would've told you otherwise.
- Mm-hmm.

228
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:44,889
I'm okay, thanks to Sir Magnus.

229
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:48,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,269
- Magnus?
- Yeah.

231
00:12:50,853 --> 00:12:52,771
- How?
- I almost got shot earlier.

232
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:54,815
But

233
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:56,775
he saved me.

234
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:01,614
- Sir.
- He would've done the same for me.

235
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:06,785
Thank you.

236
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:09,163
He reminds me of you.

237
00:13:10,706 --> 00:13:12,500
Aside from being brave,

238
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,543
he has a big heart

239
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,003
like you.

240
00:13:16,086 --> 00:13:19,340
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

241
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:21,383
Thank you for saving Liam.

242
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:24,261
You didn't back out of the fight.

243
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:27,306
You didn't abandon us.

244
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:30,184
Thank you too, sir.

245
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,395
For saving me.

246
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:40,402
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:13:48,869 --> 00:13:54,583
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

248
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:03,300
There's an exit wound. That's good.

249
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:05,761
At least the bullet didn't get stuck.

250
00:14:05,844 --> 00:14:07,555
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,932
Why is he still not waking up?

252
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:11,850
It might be loss of blood,

253
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:14,061
or he could still be in shock.

254
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:18,607
Sorry, ma'am. I'm still a nursing student.

255
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,735
What else can you do?

256
00:14:23,153 --> 00:14:24,572
Don't worry, ma'am.

257
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:27,199
You know Liam.

258
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:31,745
He's a fighter.
He won't give up that easily.

259
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:34,373
[GRETA SOBS]

260
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:36,542
My son…

261
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:41,422
[SOBBING]

262
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:47,428
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:53,642
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

264
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:01,901
Leni.

265
00:15:02,526 --> 00:15:04,069
Are you okay now, dear?

266
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:05,779
[LENI BREATHES DEEPLY]

267
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:08,198
Aren't we going home yet, Pa?

268
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:13,078
I'm sure more cops will come.

269
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:15,831
Can your men still handle them?

270
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:18,709
We still have the senator's son.

271
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:21,879
But if you want,

272
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:25,841
you and your sister can go home first.

273
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:29,803
I need to finish my mission.

274
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,931
Pa… [GRUNTS]

275
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,182
[EMIL] Careful.

276
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:37,686
Ayen's not with us on this island.

277
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:41,649
She left us a long time ago, Pa.

278
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,567
When we were still in Manila.

279
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:45,027
She's here.

280
00:15:45,861 --> 00:15:46,946
She came back.

281
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:50,991
But we fought again.

282
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:56,538
I just wanted to kill Magnus,

283
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:57,998
but she stopped me.

284
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:00,209
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

285
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:04,254
Wasn't our plan to steal money

286
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:07,841
and take revenge on Magnus?

287
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:13,180
But your sister changed her mind again.

288
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:16,934
But I…

289
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:21,146
have made up my mind.

290
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:23,023
I'm going to kill Magnus.

291
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:25,442
I'm going to kill that bastard

292
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:27,945
whether your sister likes it or not.

293
00:16:28,028 --> 00:16:32,074
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

294
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:33,534
After that,

295
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:36,870
we'll leave this island.

296
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:38,706
Okay?

297
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:41,083
We'll go somewhere far away.

298
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:44,586
We'll start a new life.

299
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:48,590
That's a promise, Leni.

300
00:16:51,677 --> 00:16:53,846
We'll live a luxurious life…

301
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:57,349
just like the Rojas.

302
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:03,981
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,878
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:29,131
[WHIMPERING]

305
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:30,799
[SCREAMS]

306
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,801
<i>Greta. Hey.</i>

307
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:36,805
[GRETA BREATHING SHAKILY]

308
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,057
<i>Ayen's back.</i>

309
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:42,811
<i>She won't stop</i>
<i>until she gets revenge on us, Magnus.</i>

310
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:45,773
<i>- Greta.</i>
<i>- What?</i>

311
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:48,650
<i>You were just having a bad dream.</i>

312
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:53,906
<i>Promise me you won't leave me.</i>

313
00:17:53,989 --> 00:17:55,365
<i>Promise me.</i>

314
00:17:57,534 --> 00:18:00,954
- <i>I won't leave you.</i>
- [GRETA SOBBING]

315
00:18:02,206 --> 00:18:03,332
[MAGNUS] <i>I won't leave you.</i>

316
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:11,048
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:18:11,131 --> 00:18:12,716
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

318
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:20,557
Liam…

319
00:18:22,726 --> 00:18:23,977
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

320
00:18:24,061 --> 00:18:25,687
Forgive me.

321
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:36,782
I didn't mean for this to happen.

322
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:43,163
It's my fault.

323
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:44,915
[VOICE BREAKING] It's all my fault.

324
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:53,215
[SOBBING]

325
00:18:57,427 --> 00:19:00,264
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

326
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:01,515
Ma?

327
00:19:01,598 --> 00:19:02,891
Liam.

328
00:19:04,309 --> 00:19:05,561
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

329
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:11,066
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

330
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:14,278
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

331
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:15,529
Don't cry anymore.

332
00:19:25,122 --> 00:19:26,290
[MACKY SCREAMS]

333
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,042
[SCREAMING]

334
00:19:30,919 --> 00:19:33,505
- [WHIP CRACKS]
- [MACKY SCREAMS]

335
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:36,049
[MACKY CRYING, GROANING]

336
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,509
Stop it!

337
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:43,390
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

338
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:46,476
- [WHIP CRACKS]
- [SCREAMS]

339
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:53,108
<i>Are we really safe?</i>

340
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:54,860
<i>The police are all over Alicante.</i>

341
00:19:54,943 --> 00:19:58,322
<i>No one in their right mind</i>
<i>would attack us here.</i>

342
00:19:58,405 --> 00:19:59,364
[STAFF SCREAMING]

343
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:05,412
<i>Ask the senator for 100 million</i>
<i>for Macky Maristella's life.</i>

344
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:07,873
[SCREAMING]

345
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:12,002
- [MACKY PANTING, SCREAMING]
- [EMIL] <i>We need him alive.</i>

346
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:16,131
[MACKY, GROANING]
<i>Oh my God! Oh my God!</i>

347
00:20:16,673 --> 00:20:21,011
<i>I can't stay mad at you for too long,</i>
<i>no matter what you do.</i>

348
00:20:21,094 --> 00:20:23,013
[GRETA] <i>Lieutenant Areza said</i>

349
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:26,308
they're getting ready
to get us off this island.

350
00:20:26,850 --> 00:20:29,519
<i>I'm glad to hear Liam's okay now.</i>

351
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:32,522
<i>I hope you and your wife</i>
<i>can figure things out as well.</i>

352
00:20:32,606 --> 00:20:35,692
<i>If you needed help,</i>
<i>why didn't you come to me?</i>

353
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:39,821
[URGENT MUSIC PLAYING]

354
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:42,616
<i>- Ice, what's wrong?</i>
<i>- Liam's wound won't stop bleeding.</i>

355
00:20:42,699 --> 00:20:44,284
<i>- What?!</i>
<i>- Come on.</i>

356
00:20:44,368 --> 00:20:45,494
<i>Let's go!</i>

357
00:20:47,829 --> 00:20:49,665
<i>Liam, stop moving.</i>

358
00:20:49,748 --> 00:20:52,584
<i>Your bleeding will increase</i>
<i>if you keep moving.</i>

359
00:20:52,668 --> 00:20:55,545
- [GROANING]
<i>- Just keep calm. Okay?</i>

360
00:20:56,755 --> 00:21:00,342
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

361
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:01,802
[PANTING]

362
00:21:01,885 --> 00:21:05,013
<i>We're gonna stop the bleeding.</i>
<i>Don't worry.</i>

363
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:06,640
<i>- I'm right here.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

364
00:21:08,558 --> 00:21:14,189
[LIAM GROANING, GRUNTING]

365
00:21:16,608 --> 00:21:23,198
[LIAM CONTINUES GROANING
AND PANTING IN PAIN]
